ce:section.ce:para:
Limiting logarithmic [70] and Job’s continuous variation methods [71] were both utilized to study the reaction stoichiometry. In the limiting logarithmic study, two plots were assorted: (i) a plot of log molar concentrations NXL (at a constant AV concentration) versus the corresponding log ΔF, and (ii) a plot of log molar concentrations AV (at a constant NXL concentration) versus the corresponding log ΔF. Two straight lines were attained with slopes of 0.53: 0.51 for the lines in plots (i) and (ii), respectively indicating a 1:1 ratio (
                           Fig. S5
                        ).
